quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,133,"And hasten towards forgiveness from your Lord and a Paradise as vast as the heavens and the earth, prepared for those mindful ňĻof Godňļ"
  3,134,"ňĻThey areňļ those who donate in prosperity and adversity, control their anger, and pardon others. And God loves the good-doers"
  3,135,"ňĻThey areňļ those who, upon committing an evil deed or wronging themselves, remember God and seek forgiveness and do not knowingly persist in sin‚ÄĒand who forgives sins except God"
  3,136,"Their reward is forgiveness from their Lord and Gardens under which rivers flow, staying there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ňĻrighteousnessňļ"
  3,137,"Similar situations came to pass before you, so travel throughout the land and see the fate of the deniers"
  3,138,This¬†is an insight to humanity‚ÄĒa guide and a lesson to the God-fearing
  3,139,"Do not falter or grieve, for you will have the upper hand, if you are ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  3,140,"If you have suffered injuries ňĻat UŠł•udňļ, they suffered similarly ňĻat Badrňļ. We alternate these days ňĻof victory and defeatňļ among people so that God may reveal the ňĻtrueňļ believers, choose martyrs from among you‚ÄĒand God does not like the wrongdoers‚ÄĒ"
  3,141,and distinguish the ňĻtrueňļ believers and destroy the disbelievers
  3,142,Do you think you will enter Paradise without God proving which of you ňĻtrulyňļ struggled ňĻfor His causeňļ and patiently endured
  3,143,"You certainly wished ňĻfor the opportunityňļ for martyrdom before encountering it, now you have seen it with your own eyes"
  3,144,"MuŠł•ammad is no more than a messenger; other messengers have gone before him. If he were to die or to be killed, would you regress into disbelief? Those who do so will not harm God whatsoever. And God will reward those who are grateful"
  3,145,"No soul can ever die without God‚Äôs Will at the destined time. Those who desire worldly gain, We will let them have it, and those who desire heavenly reward, We will grant it to them. And We will reward those who are grateful"
  3,146,"ňĻImagineňļ how many devotees fought along with their prophets and never faltered despite whatever ňĻlossesňļ they suffered in the cause of God, nor did they weaken or give in! God loves those who persevere"
  3,147,"And all they said was, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Forgive our sins and excesses, make our steps firm, and grant us victory over the disbelieving people.‚ÄĚ"
  3,148,So God gave them the reward of this world and the excellent reward of the Hereafter. For God loves the good-doers
  3,149,"O believers! If you yield to the disbelievers, they will drag you back to disbelief‚ÄĒand you will become losers"
  3,150,"But no! God is your Guardian, and He is the best Helper"
  3,151,We will cast horror into the hearts of the disbelievers for associating ňĻfalse godsňļ with God‚ÄĒa practice He has never authorized. The Fire will be their home‚ÄĒwhat an evil place for the wrongdoers to stay
  3,152,"Indeed, God fulfilled His promise to you when you ňĻinitiallyňļ swept them away by His Will, then your courage weakened and you disputed about the command and disobeyed,¬†after God had brought victory within your reach. Some of you were after worldly gain while others desired a heavenly reward. He denied you victory over them as a test, yet He has pardoned you. And God is Gracious to the believers"